dct_title_s: Map of the Tenimber Islands, after Guyots general map of the Assistant Residency Banda, illustrating the recent discovery of Egeron Strait : to accompany the paper by Profr. P. J. Veth
dct_description_sm: Conventional Dutch transcriptions of indigenous place names are shown. "The Dutch flag added to the name of a village indicates that the native chief or Urang Kaya holds a commission from the Netherlands Government." Relief shown by hachures. Depth shown by soundings. From: Journal of the Royal Geographical Society of London. Vol. 48 (1878), pp. 294-301; held in Firestone Library. Call number: G7 .J687 v.48 1878
